WEBVTT

02:33.737 --> 02:34.737
How's it look?

02:34.947 --> 02:39.116
The cop's body's about 300 yards
down in an abandoned tunnel.

02:39.618 --> 02:41.661
-Howie?
-Right behind you, captain.

02:41.912 --> 02:44.747
Keep back till
I process the scene, okay?

04:01.366 --> 04:03.242
Watch out! It's falling!

05:14.064 --> 05:15.940
So where the hell is the car?

05:16.233 --> 05:17.400
I don't know.

05:18.235 --> 05:21.028
That's the last time
I take a goddamn redeye.

05:21.238 --> 05:22.238
We can take a cab.

05:23.073 --> 05:27.076
I'm gonna fire this son of a bitch.
He's always got some excuse.

05:32.332 --> 05:35.167
Well, come on.
We'll be home before you know it.

05:35.335 --> 05:36.627
Yeah.

06:16.626 --> 06:17.835
Excuse me?

06:18.086 --> 06:20.629
Excuse me,
I think you're going the wrong way.

06:20.881 --> 06:22.298
Excuse me.

06:23.467 --> 06:26.010
Honey. Honey. Honey, wake up.

06:26.219 --> 06:28.512
We're lost
or he's taking us for a ride.

06:29.473 --> 06:31.474
We're in the middle of nowhere.

06:31.892 --> 06:34.018
Where the hell you going?
I said Fifth Avenue.

06:37.314 --> 06:39.815
We're not tourists here, man!

06:40.317 --> 06:42.359
Hey, where are you going?

06:50.202 --> 06:52.328
Let us out. Stop the car!

06:53.830 --> 06:55.915
Stop this car!

07:07.344 --> 07:08.344
Shit!

07:09.054 --> 07:10.054
Oh, my God.

07:10.347 --> 07:11.847
Son of a bitch!

07:12.182 --> 07:14.266
Stop the goddamn car!

07:23.860 --> 07:25.361
-Please!
-Stop the car!

07:27.030 --> 07:28.656
Stop this car, goddamn it!

07:29.199 --> 07:30.199
Stop this car!

07:33.662 --> 07:35.037
Good morning.

07:36.790 --> 07:40.292
You're looking a little dehydrated.
How about some juice?

07:40.544 --> 07:42.586
How about two fingers of vodka?

07:42.921 --> 07:45.297
A little early for vodka,
don't you think?

07:45.549 --> 07:47.925
Time, as you know,
is a relative consideration.

07:48.718 --> 07:52.388
-Juice.
-Vodka.

07:52.556 --> 07:54.140
Juice.

07:54.307 --> 07:56.475
-Coming!
-Join me in a drink, Richard?

07:56.726 --> 08:00.229
I'd love to. But a med-tech
with liquor on his breath? l think not.

08:00.730 --> 08:03.065
-Thanks.
-So how are you?

08:03.400 --> 08:05.734
I'm better than
your heart-pacing gear.

08:05.986 --> 08:09.697
Every time, it's skewed further out
of spec. You really need a new unit.

08:09.906 --> 08:11.699
I really need a new body.

08:12.325 --> 08:16.579
I can't help you with that,
but I'll bring a new unit by tomorrow.

08:16.788 --> 08:18.455
This'll be stable till then.

08:18.707 --> 08:20.583
-Thank you.
-You take it easy.

08:20.917 --> 08:23.252
I'll take it any way I can get it.

08:24.212 --> 08:27.590
-How's he doing?
-He asked for vodka again.

08:27.841 --> 08:29.925
-Did you give him any?
-No.

08:30.594 --> 08:33.011
-Good morning, doctor.
-Hi, Richard.

08:33.304 --> 08:35.514
Hey, would you look at this?

08:36.600 --> 08:40.102
-A peregrine falcon, am l right?
-Yup.

08:40.812 --> 08:41.979
He likes cripples.

08:43.440 --> 08:45.774
There was a piece about them
in The Times the other day...

08:45.942 --> 08:47.943
...nesting all over the city.

08:48.278 --> 08:51.989
Something about the architecture
of these old New York buildings.

08:52.657 --> 08:54.325
I thought he liked my company.

08:58.872 --> 09:02.041
They're a little shy.
Don't take it personally.

09:02.292 --> 09:03.459
Can l get you a drink?

09:03.752 --> 09:05.127
No, thanks. l'm fine.

09:06.463 --> 09:07.630
Bed mode.

09:16.806 --> 09:19.266
-Got vodka in there?
-No.

09:19.476 --> 09:21.769
And you ain't getting any either.

09:22.771 --> 09:24.980
All right, l'll let you guys talk.

09:27.359 --> 09:31.403
So you can imagine how much sleep
I've gotten the past few days...

09:31.655 --> 09:33.489
...considering your request.

09:33.865 --> 09:36.992
Since I made my decision,
I've been sleeping like a baby.

09:37.202 --> 09:40.996
After all you have survived,
beat all the odds...

09:41.289 --> 09:44.708
...you know there's work
on nerve regeneration every day.

09:45.168 --> 09:49.797
One finger, two shoulders and a brain.
That's all l have, Barry.

09:50.799 --> 09:53.717
These dysreflexia seizures
are occurring more often.

09:54.386 --> 09:58.013
The buildup of fluid in my spine
is a degenerative condition.

09:58.181 --> 10:01.934
We know I'm waiting for the seizure
that'll make me a vegetable.

10:04.562 --> 10:06.855
I don't wanna be a vegetable, Barry.

10:09.192 --> 10:12.569
I want to make the final transition
on my own terms.

10:15.365 --> 10:17.700
I'll get it done with or without you.

10:18.910 --> 10:22.329
Yeah. Yeah, l suppose you would.

10:27.252 --> 10:28.377
So?

10:33.383 --> 10:35.592
-Okay.
-Okay what?

10:39.556 --> 10:41.974
Okay, l'll assist you...

10:42.976 --> 10:45.060
-...in your final transition.
-Today?

10:45.353 --> 10:48.897
There are preparations to be made.
This is not a flu shot.

10:49.065 --> 10:51.400
My business is in order.
My bags are packed.

10:51.609 --> 10:54.236
Besides, l've got
a medical conference to go to.

10:54.446 --> 10:55.988
I've got a plane to catch.

10:56.281 --> 10:57.740
You're lying.

10:58.867 --> 11:00.075
When do you get back?

11:01.745 --> 11:02.911
Sunday.

11:03.079 --> 11:06.373
Okay. Sunday.

11:09.878 --> 11:11.128
I'll see you then.

11:11.588 --> 11:13.589
Get out before you change your mind.

11:16.426 --> 11:18.469
Don't get up. l'll show myself out.

11:18.762 --> 11:20.929
Yeah, l'll race you to the door.

11:21.514 --> 11:22.598
Barry....

11:25.393 --> 11:26.602
You are...

11:28.271 --> 11:30.105
...a very good friend.

12:20.949 --> 12:22.491
Amelia?

12:23.368 --> 12:26.578
-Hey.
-Hey.

12:26.746 --> 12:28.330
Morning.

12:28.665 --> 12:29.998
You okay?

12:30.208 --> 12:33.252
Yeah, l'm fine.
I just couldn't sleep.

12:37.090 --> 12:39.716
-What time is it?
-lt's early.

12:49.018 --> 12:51.019
I'll be late for work. I gotta shower.

12:51.271 --> 12:52.896
No, you don't. Stay here.

12:53.773 --> 12:55.023
I gotta go.

13:07.537 --> 13:08.745
Make breakfast?

13:09.038 --> 13:11.623
No, thanks. l'm gonna be late.

13:11.875 --> 13:14.751
Another slam-bam-thank-you-ma'am?

13:17.755 --> 13:19.131
All right, look....

13:20.758 --> 13:22.551
My therapist tells me...

13:22.719 --> 13:25.637
...l might not be getting what l need
out of this relationship.

13:25.889 --> 13:27.389
What are we doing here?

13:27.640 --> 13:30.434
I think you and me,
we make a great couple.

13:32.145 --> 13:34.313
You know where I stand on this.

13:34.564 --> 13:35.898
You know what l want.

13:36.316 --> 13:38.317
Steve, we've been through this.

13:39.235 --> 13:41.236
All right? l care about you.

13:41.738 --> 13:43.739
I can't make a commitment.

13:53.082 --> 13:55.250
Well, go to work then.

13:56.336 --> 13:58.128
You're gonna be late.

14:10.934 --> 14:14.770
-You're quitting the cops?
-l'm transferring to Youth Services.

14:14.979 --> 14:17.940
Lucky fuck. You must
have one hell of a rabbi.

14:18.149 --> 14:20.651
-We're gonna miss you.
-3-post-1 1 here.

14:20.944 --> 14:22.778
<i>Frightened child at Amtrak site.</i>

14:23.071 --> 14:24.321
I'll take it.

14:24.697 --> 14:26.949
Kid found something
over at the tracks.

14:27.158 --> 14:30.285
-Finish eating. I'll check it out.
-See you, kid.

14:57.230 --> 14:59.856
<i>3-post-1 1 ,</i>
<i>anything further on that 1 0-1 0?</i>

15:00.108 --> 15:01.525
Nothing yet.

15:03.820 --> 15:05.320
Wait. l think I see him.

15:06.698 --> 15:09.241
Are you the one
who called the police?

15:52.201 --> 15:53.702
Wait there, okay?

16:59.602 --> 17:00.936
Are you out of your mind?

17:01.104 --> 17:02.938
Just shut off the engine.

17:03.231 --> 17:06.273
There's been a homicide.
I can't let you through.

17:18.746 --> 17:20.038
I'm Amelia.
What's your name?

17:20.289 --> 17:22.582
-Chris.
-Chris. Hey.

17:22.750 --> 17:25.794
I got a job for you.
Here's money.

17:26.128 --> 17:29.631
I need you to buy me one of
those cheapo cardboard cameras.

17:29.799 --> 17:32.008
You know,
the ones you can throw away?

17:32.343 --> 17:33.844
Okay. Fast as you can.

17:40.893 --> 17:42.185
3-post-1 1 to Central.

19:37.260 --> 19:39.761
Captain Cheney, Detective Solomon.

19:40.096 --> 19:42.973
First officer on the scene
is over there.

19:43.474 --> 19:45.392
--on the tracks near the body.

19:45.810 --> 19:48.270
I collected it
before it was washed away.

19:51.440 --> 19:53.942
-l also took some pictures.
-Thanks.

19:54.193 --> 19:56.152
You stopped the train?

19:56.404 --> 19:58.947
It might have disturbed
the physical evidence.

19:59.156 --> 20:02.033
Why not shut down Grand Central
while you're at it?

20:02.285 --> 20:04.286
Patrolman Donahue. ls that right?

20:04.495 --> 20:05.620
Donaghy.

20:06.038 --> 20:08.957
-A rookie, l take it.
-No, sir.

20:09.834 --> 20:11.001
Pretty dumb.

20:12.128 --> 20:14.796
Captain, guess who the vic is?

20:15.006 --> 20:17.048
-Talk to me.
-Alan fucking Rubin.

20:17.300 --> 20:19.759
-Mister "Rebuild New York" himself?
-Yeah.

20:19.927 --> 20:21.219
Great.

20:21.929 --> 20:26.016
No one enters this area
except for my crime scene guys.

20:36.652 --> 20:38.820
Knight to H6. Check.

20:41.157 --> 20:43.491
You got company. Cops.

20:43.701 --> 20:46.703
-Tell them l'm busy.
-They said it was urgent.

20:46.954 --> 20:48.204
Tell them l'm out running.

20:49.165 --> 20:50.874
She's too polite for that, Linc.

20:51.083 --> 20:53.752
Hey, look who's here!

20:56.339 --> 20:58.340
I caught a serious situation.

20:58.549 --> 21:00.342
It's going around, Paulie.

21:00.593 --> 21:02.677
Chief Murphy sent me.

21:04.180 --> 21:05.180
The good chief.

21:07.183 --> 21:11.186
Heard about that couple at the airport?
Got in a taxi, never got home?

21:11.979 --> 21:13.063
He don't watch the news.

21:13.356 --> 21:16.858
You used to read four papers a day
and tape the news shows.

21:17.026 --> 21:19.861
Yeah, now l just hit
the rewind button. A3.

21:20.071 --> 21:21.404
Things never change.

21:21.697 --> 21:24.532
That was Alan Rubin
and his wife in that taxi.

21:25.368 --> 21:27.786
They found him dead,
buried, shot in the face...

21:28.037 --> 21:32.040
...hand sticking out of the ground
with his wife's ring on his finger...

21:32.208 --> 21:33.875
...which was skinned to the bone.

21:34.543 --> 21:35.877
She's still missing.

21:36.045 --> 21:37.796
Excuse me while you catch up.

21:38.047 --> 21:39.255
Don't go too far.

21:39.507 --> 21:43.009
We'll be letting these nice
gentlemen out in 30 seconds.

21:43.636 --> 21:46.554
Sounds like you got yourself
an open-and-shut there.

21:46.764 --> 21:48.264
I don't think so.

21:48.516 --> 21:50.892
A man worth several hundred
million found dead...

21:51.060 --> 21:53.812
...his wife's ring
on his mutilated hand.

21:54.563 --> 21:56.106
What's that tell you?

21:56.774 --> 21:59.150
The doer is saying he's got her.

21:59.610 --> 22:02.320
He's probably making
a ransom demand right now.

22:03.072 --> 22:05.782
-l'd have been paged.
-Check your batteries.

22:06.534 --> 22:08.243
It's definitely a ransom.

22:10.162 --> 22:12.789
Excuse me, Mr. Rhyme.
Kenneth Solomon.

22:13.249 --> 22:18.253
I've read all your books. Scene of
the Crime, at least a dozen times.

22:18.838 --> 22:20.255
It's great to meet you.

22:22.049 --> 22:25.635
-Where do you find these guys?
-They wanna work with the best.

22:26.303 --> 22:30.598
I guess now you're gonna ask me
to discuss the crime scene with you.

22:31.350 --> 22:35.145
We got a bunch of physical evidence
that doesn't exactly make sense.

22:35.438 --> 22:38.773
Some seriously weird stuff.
It's all in the report.

22:40.901 --> 22:43.194
-Thelma?
-You okay?

22:45.990 --> 22:47.574
-Linc, you okay?
-Out! Now!

22:47.783 --> 22:51.119
-Anything we can do?
-Asses out of here now!

22:51.287 --> 22:54.372
Let me get you some air.
Come on. Breathe for me.

22:56.333 --> 22:57.625
I said out!

22:58.335 --> 23:01.671
Come on. Deep breaths.
Deep breaths. Come on.

23:01.881 --> 23:04.215
Deep breaths.
I'm getting a BP on you.

23:04.467 --> 23:05.633
You gotta breathe.

23:05.843 --> 23:07.886
Look at me. Breathe.

23:11.807 --> 23:14.976
Look at me. Deep breaths.
Come on. Come on.

23:15.227 --> 23:17.479
You gotta take this oxygen.

23:17.646 --> 23:18.897
Stay with me.

23:19.607 --> 23:22.692
Come on. You can do it.
Don't go out on me now.

23:22.985 --> 23:24.736
Come on. Look at me.

23:49.678 --> 23:50.804
Thelma?

23:54.225 --> 23:56.518
-Thelma?
-You okay?

23:57.353 --> 24:01.064
I would be okay if your powers
of resuscitation were less adept.

24:02.066 --> 24:04.526
Look, not on my shift, all right?

24:04.735 --> 24:07.237
If you have a problem,
you can fire my ass.

24:07.446 --> 24:10.740
I provide for you in my will.
You ought to keep that in mind.

24:11.075 --> 24:15.787
Rhyme, I'm not interested in
having this conversation. Okay?

24:16.038 --> 24:17.413
-Okay.
-Okay.

24:17.581 --> 24:19.916
The crime scene report
Sellitto left....

24:20.209 --> 24:23.378
Could you take the photos
and load them in the viewer?

24:23.587 --> 24:25.046
View scan.

24:30.970 --> 24:34.222
Let's take a look at what we got here.

24:35.808 --> 24:37.183
Where it says location....

24:38.227 --> 24:41.729
Now what's that--?
What's it say about that newspaper?

24:42.106 --> 24:45.275
"Newspaper found beneath
a coarse-thread hex bolt...

24:45.568 --> 24:47.986
-...with 4 p.m. circled on it."
-Four p.m.

24:49.238 --> 24:52.949
Zoom.

24:55.077 --> 24:58.580
What about that piece of paper?
What's the number on there?

24:58.914 --> 25:01.249
"A torn book page with 1 1 9 on it."

25:01.750 --> 25:06.337
1 1 9, 4 p.m.

25:10.759 --> 25:12.427
1 1-9. What's today's date?

25:12.970 --> 25:14.762
Today's November 9.

25:15.431 --> 25:16.431
Phone mode.

25:16.807 --> 25:18.933
Sellitto, Paulie. Call.

25:23.731 --> 25:24.731
What?

25:27.651 --> 25:30.778
Sad fact is, a huge percentage
of inner-city kids...

25:30.946 --> 25:33.281
...have their
first drug experiences...

25:33.616 --> 25:35.950
...at the fifth grade level.

25:38.454 --> 25:41.456
Here are some of the drugs
they'll most likely be offered.

25:44.501 --> 25:45.960
Marijuana.

25:46.795 --> 25:49.464
How'd you like to get your hands
on that briefcase?

25:49.757 --> 25:51.174
Barbiturates.

25:51.842 --> 25:52.884
Amphetamines.

25:53.761 --> 25:55.136
Cocaine.

25:56.180 --> 25:57.847
Rock cocaine.

26:07.691 --> 26:10.777
-What's this about?
-You know who Lincoln Rhyme is?

26:10.986 --> 26:13.279
-What? The textbook guy?
-Yeah.

26:13.489 --> 26:16.991
-So what does that have to do with me?
-You'll find out.

26:20.704 --> 26:22.538
Come on in. They're right in there.

26:25.918 --> 26:28.294
A patrol cop took these pictures?

26:28.504 --> 26:31.381
Yeah, first one on the scene.
It started to rain.

26:31.548 --> 26:32.548
Smart cop.

26:32.800 --> 26:36.386
Had the balls to stop an Amtrak
from running over the crime scene.

26:36.595 --> 26:38.721
Here she is now.
Officer Donahoe...

26:39.348 --> 26:40.807
...meet Lincoln Rhyme.

26:41.016 --> 26:42.225
Donaghy.

26:46.563 --> 26:48.356
You took terrific photographs.

26:50.025 --> 26:51.609
You know who l am?

26:52.111 --> 26:54.362
I read your manual at the academy.

26:54.530 --> 26:55.530
What'd you think?

26:56.532 --> 26:57.865
I'm not a book critic.

26:58.826 --> 26:59.909
You found it useful?

27:00.703 --> 27:01.703
Yeah, l guess so.

27:01.912 --> 27:04.330
Sure you did.
You stopped that train.

27:04.957 --> 27:06.624
The photos you took.

27:07.876 --> 27:10.628
I'd say you have
a natural instinct for forensics.

27:11.213 --> 27:13.339
So what do we got, Paulie?

27:14.883 --> 27:18.219
We have footprints, size 1 0,
thanks to Officer Donaghy...

27:18.429 --> 27:20.888
...using a dollar bill
to establish scale.

27:21.056 --> 27:23.766
We have asbestos
where there shouldn't be any.

27:23.976 --> 27:27.437
An iron bolt holding down
a piece of paper...

27:27.646 --> 27:30.648
...a book page
with 1 1 9 written on it.

27:30.983 --> 27:32.775
Decaying oxidation on the bolt...

27:32.985 --> 27:35.903
<i>...but none on the thread.</i>
<i>Someone removed it...</i>

27:36.238 --> 27:37.572
...from somewhere else...

27:37.740 --> 27:41.075
<i>...and placed it there recently.</i>
<i>Wouldn't you agree, officer?</i>

27:41.368 --> 27:43.953
Wouldn't you agree,
Officer Donaghy?

27:48.000 --> 27:50.960
Paulie, l'm convinced
this crime scene was staged.

27:51.587 --> 27:53.880
-Perp's telling us something.
-What?

27:54.256 --> 27:56.924
Book, page 1 1 9. 1 1 -9.
That's today's date.

27:57.176 --> 27:59.510
Newspaper, 4 p.m.
What time you got?

27:59.678 --> 28:00.678
1 2:1 5.

28:02.264 --> 28:03.473
She's alive.

28:04.099 --> 28:07.018
-And he's gonna kill her at 4?
-P.M.

28:09.438 --> 28:11.105
We have your interest yet?

28:14.485 --> 28:17.111
I want you to work the case with us.

28:17.321 --> 28:18.946
It's not my area.

28:19.907 --> 28:22.116
Are you being modest, or are you...

28:22.284 --> 28:24.827
...uneasy about doing
some real police work?

28:26.413 --> 28:27.538
Excuse me?

28:27.790 --> 28:29.791
What department do you work in?

28:30.209 --> 28:32.960
Youth Services.
I picked her up at orientation.

28:33.170 --> 28:34.962
I see. Youth Services.

28:35.464 --> 28:38.174
I wait-listed a year,
and l won't jeopardise--

28:38.425 --> 28:40.051
Jeopardise what?

28:41.303 --> 28:42.637
Cushy desk job?

28:42.805 --> 28:45.681
-Forensics is not my area.
-l disagree with you.

28:46.058 --> 28:48.810
Well, you can't force me
to take this assignment.

28:51.188 --> 28:52.355
I can.

28:53.440 --> 28:54.482
And if l refuse?

28:54.650 --> 28:56.818
You're putting your career at risk.

28:57.069 --> 29:00.154
You think because of your condition
you can push people around?

29:00.489 --> 29:02.323
That is truly pathetic.

29:03.367 --> 29:04.367
Truly?

29:04.576 --> 29:06.577
Yeah, damn right. Truly.

29:06.829 --> 29:08.663
Well, forgive me truly...

29:09.331 --> 29:12.375
...if I insist on having
someone with your brains...

29:12.668 --> 29:16.546
...and a fresh pair of eyes.
There's a life at stake here, officer.

29:17.840 --> 29:20.007
We'll need key people
and tech support.

29:20.509 --> 29:22.009
-l know the guys.
-Okay.

29:23.971 --> 29:25.972
What the hell you smiling at?

29:35.899 --> 29:37.567
Pull up a chair.

29:37.776 --> 29:40.987
Tell me everything you know
about the crime scene.

29:41.697 --> 29:42.864
It's in my report.

29:43.282 --> 29:47.201
I read your report.
I want to know what you felt...

29:47.536 --> 29:49.078
...what you feel...

29:50.038 --> 29:52.373
...in the deepest recesses
of your senses.

29:52.791 --> 29:56.002
You are in love with the sound
of your voice, aren't you?

29:56.211 --> 29:59.505
It's your voice I want to hear.
Pull up a chair. l won't bite.

30:27.826 --> 30:30.912
