34:10.841 --> 34:13.300
-l'm not sure.
-Can you individuate it?

34:13.635 --> 34:15.136
If l had an EDX, I could.

34:15.637 --> 34:17.972
We don't have
a goddamn E-the-fuck-X.

34:18.556 --> 34:22.016
Look who forgot their chill pill
this morning. Excuse me.

34:22.268 --> 34:27.063
Come on. l'm all over this thing now.
Okay, we're talking...

34:27.858 --> 34:29.275
...pearly-looking.

34:30.068 --> 34:31.860
Some kind of a...

34:32.154 --> 34:34.572
...shellfish or something.

34:36.824 --> 34:38.409
Oyster shells, maybe?

34:40.078 --> 34:41.620
Could be.

34:43.415 --> 34:46.876
Definitely. lf l had to bet on it,
I'd say it was. Sure.

34:50.005 --> 34:53.174
I got it. The oldest asbestos
sites are coming up now.

35:23.455 --> 35:27.708
In 1 91 3, when the Woolworth Building
was being built...

35:27.876 --> 35:31.337
...workmen found the body of
a rich industrialist, Talbot Soames.

35:32.380 --> 35:36.050
He'd been kidnapped, shot and buried
in what they thought was sand.

35:36.259 --> 35:39.887
Turned out to be oyster shells.
Crushed oyster shells.

35:40.096 --> 35:43.057
That's what they used as
landfill in lower Manhattan.

35:43.225 --> 35:44.934
That's how Pearl Street got its name.

35:45.101 --> 35:48.562
That's where Mrs. Rubin's
gonna be, somewhere downtown.

35:48.980 --> 35:51.065
She'll be underground.

35:51.274 --> 35:53.609
She'll be in a basement...

35:53.902 --> 35:56.278
...near or in the Woolworth Building.

35:56.488 --> 36:00.783
Have Emergency Services Unit
meet us by the Woolworth Building.

36:00.992 --> 36:03.577
Tell them to start their search.
We may get lucky.

36:04.371 --> 36:05.913
Eddie, did you bring your van?

36:06.164 --> 36:07.957
-lt's downstairs.
-We'll need it.

36:08.291 --> 36:11.168
Throw your keys to Amelia.
You guys go with her.

36:11.419 --> 36:12.461
Should I go too?

36:12.671 --> 36:14.964
You stay here with me
and work that bolt.

36:15.173 --> 36:16.423
That's the missing piece.

36:16.633 --> 36:18.259
Should we keep Cheney in the loop?

36:18.760 --> 36:20.803
-Fuck him.
-Fuck him.

36:24.599 --> 36:25.599
Amelia.

36:26.601 --> 36:28.269
Just trust me.

36:29.104 --> 36:32.815
Just follow those instincts
you were born with. l'll be with you...

36:33.275 --> 36:35.276
...every step of the way.

36:45.620 --> 36:47.788
Jesus, 25 minutes left.

36:49.332 --> 36:53.294
-How did Rhyme get that way?
-He was born brilliant. It happens.

36:54.045 --> 36:55.963
I mean, the physical part.

36:57.299 --> 37:00.134
Four years ago, he was working
the body of a cop...

37:00.343 --> 37:02.636
...they'd found shot
in a subway tunnel.

37:03.471 --> 37:06.181
Beam came down
and damn near cut him in half.

37:06.683 --> 37:07.850
Jesus.

37:10.145 --> 37:11.145
Family?

37:12.480 --> 37:13.647
Sister in Phoenix.

37:14.357 --> 37:16.984
He never sees her.
Cut himself off.

37:17.861 --> 37:20.821
Technically, he's still on
active duty collecting pay.

37:21.072 --> 37:23.949
Insurance picks up
24-hour care and the gadgets.

37:24.159 --> 37:27.494
On weekends, always one or two cops
there lending a hand.

37:27.746 --> 37:30.456
-Tough deal.
-You won't hear him complaining.

37:30.665 --> 37:33.042
He likes pushing
other people's buttons.

37:33.251 --> 37:35.586
In your case, that's a compliment.

37:35.837 --> 37:40.007
You gotta learn to relax around
a compliment, especially from Rhyme.

37:40.175 --> 37:42.593
-You can be a little grating.
-Me?

37:42.844 --> 37:46.096
Kiddo, if you were any more
wound up, you'd be a Timex.

37:51.353 --> 37:55.397
He was a human dynamo, writing
books, lecturing all over the world...

37:55.690 --> 37:59.568
...giving expert opinion in trials,
working crimes in the city.

37:59.778 --> 38:01.278
You know what he'd do for fun?

38:01.613 --> 38:03.280
No, I can't imagine.

38:03.531 --> 38:06.492
He'd collect things.
Dirt, metals, plastics...

38:06.701 --> 38:09.787
...hubcaps, plants, musical strings...

38:10.038 --> 38:11.914
...medical tools, anything.

38:12.207 --> 38:13.374
Obsessive.

38:13.583 --> 38:17.544
He'd analyse and catalogue it
for his, what you call it, database.

38:18.964 --> 38:23.050
Jesus Christ! l'd like to get there
in one piece if possible.

38:48.410 --> 38:51.912
-New York Security Gate Company.
-That's good. What else?

38:52.163 --> 38:54.248
Nicholas Steven Gerard, elevators.

38:54.457 --> 38:56.166
-No, underground.
-A subway builder.

38:57.043 --> 38:59.920
-Subway builder sounds--
-Excuse me! N.S.G.

39:00.088 --> 39:04.758
"Niagara Steam Generation. Bought
by Eastern Gas and Electric in 1 928.

39:05.093 --> 39:09.096
The six-inch iron bolt was used
mainly for steam pipe assemblies."

39:55.810 --> 39:57.978
<i>You got 1 1 minutes.</i>
<i>Where are you?</i>

39:58.646 --> 40:00.856
<i>We just hit the financial district.</i>

40:01.149 --> 40:03.192
There's a steam junction...

40:03.401 --> 40:05.611
...with big asbestos-coated pipes.

40:05.987 --> 40:08.322
That's where she'll be.
I'd bet my legs on it.

40:08.531 --> 40:10.491
She'll be at Wall and Nassau.

40:10.825 --> 40:13.911
<i>-Wall and Nassau.</i>
-Has ESU been notified?

40:14.162 --> 40:16.497
<i>On their way.</i>
<i>They'll get there first.</i>

40:16.831 --> 40:20.834
Steam is released through
that junction every day at 4 p.m.

40:21.503 --> 40:23.670
Shit, what's this asshole up to?

40:23.922 --> 40:26.840
<i>l don't know, but it'll happen</i>
<i>in about 1 0 minutes.</i>

40:28.259 --> 40:30.344
We're here.
We're going down there.

40:34.849 --> 40:35.849
<i>Amelia?</i>

40:37.227 --> 40:38.227
Yeah, l'm here.

40:38.686 --> 40:42.022
It's their job to save Mrs. Rubin.
It's yours to get ready...

40:42.232 --> 40:44.733
<i>...and work the crime scene</i>
<i>if necessary.</i>

40:46.861 --> 40:50.030
<i>There's some things you'll need.</i>
<i>Look in the truck.</i>

40:50.448 --> 40:53.283
You'll see an aluminium suitcase...

40:54.035 --> 40:55.661
...and a radio headset.

40:56.704 --> 40:57.704
See it?

40:57.956 --> 40:59.540
<i>Yeah, l see them.</i>

41:21.437 --> 41:23.313
There must be a way in.

41:25.066 --> 41:28.735
-What's the problem here?
-Fucking valves freeze up easy.

41:29.237 --> 41:30.571
Come on. Shut it off!

41:30.822 --> 41:31.905
You there?

41:32.490 --> 41:33.574
<i>l'm here.</i>

41:34.576 --> 41:36.243
I'm inside the pipe.

41:42.208 --> 41:43.250
Go!

41:45.920 --> 41:47.337
I think I hear something.

41:47.589 --> 41:48.964
I hear something!

41:49.632 --> 41:52.593
<i>What's that? Someone's there.</i>
<i>l hear her crying!</i>

41:53.595 --> 41:55.429
Everyone, quiet now!

42:06.107 --> 42:11.945
Mrs. Rubin?

42:15.950 --> 42:16.950
She's there.

42:17.368 --> 42:18.785
<i>Mrs. Rubin!</i>

42:18.995 --> 42:20.954
We're on our way in now!

42:21.122 --> 42:22.623
Come on, guys. Come on.

42:22.832 --> 42:25.375
Let's go! Let's go!
Let's hurry the fuck up!

42:27.462 --> 42:29.004
Get a drill and a tap.

42:29.255 --> 42:31.131
Somebody cut this halfway through.

42:31.341 --> 42:33.383
<i>There's no way to turn it off.</i>

42:57.325 --> 42:58.367
Back!

43:32.360 --> 43:36.697
Paulie?

43:40.994 --> 43:44.037
Linc, she's gone.

43:44.205 --> 43:46.873
<i>The whole place is scalded in steam.</i>

43:47.208 --> 43:48.834
Let's go! Move away!

43:50.378 --> 43:54.089
ESU are gonna blow a hole
in the subbasement wall.

43:54.549 --> 43:58.260
I understand l'm working
with Chief Murphy's authorization.

43:58.720 --> 43:59.720
That's right.

43:59.929 --> 44:04.224
<i>l don't want Emergency Services guys</i>
<i>in there trampling the evidence...</i>

44:04.392 --> 44:05.934
...before we run the scene.

44:06.144 --> 44:07.144
<i>What do you want?</i>

44:07.562 --> 44:10.063
When they blow the hole,
I want Donaghy in first.

44:10.440 --> 44:14.735
She's not trained for this.
We could get our asses in a sling.

44:14.944 --> 44:17.571
<i>My ass has been</i>
<i>in a sling for four years.</i>

44:17.905 --> 44:20.907
Tell Hanson and his beasts
that's what l want. Period.

44:21.409 --> 44:23.285
All right. You got it.

44:31.085 --> 44:32.502
Okay, let's move!

44:42.889 --> 44:46.892
I'm doing this under protest.
The perp could still be in there!

44:47.101 --> 44:49.770
Rhyme's in charge,
and they're his orders.

44:50.438 --> 44:53.398
You can't handle it in there,
get your ass out.

44:53.608 --> 44:56.109
<i>-Amelia, you ready?</i>
-Yeah.

44:56.319 --> 44:57.944
You listen to me.

44:59.113 --> 45:01.656
I'm with you every step of the way.

45:02.825 --> 45:03.950
Go on.

45:05.036 --> 45:06.286
Good luck.

45:17.465 --> 45:20.217
<i>-l'm in.</i>
-Tell me what you see.

45:27.475 --> 45:29.810
<i>Everything's been boiled to hell.</i>

45:34.982 --> 45:36.316
Oh, God.

45:36.692 --> 45:37.984
<i>What is it?</i>

45:39.070 --> 45:41.071
It's an awful smell.

45:42.323 --> 45:43.490
Means you're close.

46:07.223 --> 46:09.057
I can't believe l'm doing this.

46:09.350 --> 46:10.684
<i>You're fine.</i>

46:11.185 --> 46:15.063
Just fine. You're doing great.
Now, just remember the academy.

46:15.731 --> 46:16.731
When you walk...

46:17.358 --> 46:21.570
<i>...move in a straight line. Don't</i>
<i>disturb any footprints he's left.</i>

46:21.863 --> 46:23.864
Yeah, assuming he's gone.

46:32.248 --> 46:34.040
<i>There's no footprints.</i>

46:34.500 --> 46:36.042
<i>There's nothing yet.</i>

46:51.559 --> 46:53.059
Oh, God.

46:53.686 --> 46:54.728
What?

46:55.813 --> 46:57.230
<i>Talk to me.</i>

46:58.399 --> 46:59.941
<i>Talk to me, Amelia.</i>

47:00.610 --> 47:02.402
I can see her.

47:08.075 --> 47:10.118
The steam pipe was opened...

47:10.411 --> 47:12.829
<i>...and she's tied down</i>
<i>right in front of it.</i>

47:13.247 --> 47:14.748
Okay.

47:14.957 --> 47:18.668
There's nothing you can do.
You can't do anything but help her...

47:18.920 --> 47:22.047
...by working the crime scene.
That's your job.

47:22.256 --> 47:25.342
<i>Open your suitcase.</i>
<i>Get your camera.</i>

48:08.719 --> 48:09.886
I can't do this.

48:10.846 --> 48:12.472
You can do it. Yes, you can.

48:12.682 --> 48:16.309
Yesterday you stopped a train.
You can do anything you want.

48:17.144 --> 48:19.145
Don't work me, Rhyme.

48:25.027 --> 48:26.903
<i>Just tell me what to do next.</i>

48:27.154 --> 48:30.031
Very slowly, walk the grid...

48:30.825 --> 48:33.159
<i>...one foot in front of the other.</i>

48:37.999 --> 48:41.042
<i>l want you to look around you now.</i>

48:41.252 --> 48:45.130
Crime scenes are three-dimensional.
Floors, walls and ceilings.

48:52.680 --> 48:53.680
Rhyme.

48:54.056 --> 48:55.432
<i>Yeah, l'm here.</i>

48:57.393 --> 48:59.185
There's something strange.

49:00.271 --> 49:02.147
<i>Things he left for us?</i>

49:06.944 --> 49:07.944
Yes.

49:08.863 --> 49:10.655
<i>ln a cluster again?</i>

49:10.865 --> 49:12.240
<i>A piece of wood...</i>

49:12.783 --> 49:14.868
<i>...and looks like some hair.</i>

49:15.161 --> 49:19.539
I'll walk you through collecting
the evidence. Do exactly as I say.

49:31.093 --> 49:32.552
Oh, Jesus.

49:32.762 --> 49:34.429
<i>Talk to me.</i>

49:34.680 --> 49:36.806
-lt's a bloody bone.
<i>-Where is it?</i>

49:38.893 --> 49:40.894
It's in my fucking hand.

49:41.729 --> 49:42.771
<i>Human?</i>

49:46.317 --> 49:48.068
I think so. Yeah.

49:48.736 --> 49:49.986
Photograph it.

49:50.780 --> 49:51.946
<i>Bag it.</i>

50:10.508 --> 50:11.966
Okay, that's it.

50:12.343 --> 50:13.843
I'm out of here.

50:14.428 --> 50:16.262
<i>One more thing.</i>

50:16.931 --> 50:18.765
We gotta process the body.

50:19.475 --> 50:22.811
<i>What? l'm not a medical examiner.</i>
<i>l can't do that.</i>

50:23.020 --> 50:24.479
<i>lt's not an autopsy.</i>

50:24.772 --> 50:26.606
I just want you to....

50:27.358 --> 50:29.234
Just describe the restraints.

50:43.040 --> 50:44.958
They're strange-looking handcuffs.

50:45.167 --> 50:48.044
They look more like
old shackles or something.

50:52.133 --> 50:54.968
<i>And there's a chain across her waist.</i>

50:56.262 --> 50:59.139
And her feet are bound with a rope.

51:01.809 --> 51:03.685
<i>Hands above her head?</i>

51:04.645 --> 51:06.020
Yeah.

51:10.192 --> 51:12.485
There's also a large
piece of flesh...

51:12.695 --> 51:15.363
<i>...missing from her right forearm.</i>

51:16.365 --> 51:19.784
It's right down to the bone.
It was surgically removed.

51:21.287 --> 51:22.829
This is what l want you to do.

51:23.330 --> 51:25.707
We're gonna need those handcuffs.

51:26.083 --> 51:29.169
<i>lt's probably our best chance</i>
<i>for good prints.</i>

51:29.420 --> 51:31.421
The M.E. can remove them.

51:31.672 --> 51:35.425
M.E. is all thumbs.
They'll mess up the prints.

51:35.676 --> 51:39.220
Look in the suitcase.
There's a small saw.

51:47.813 --> 51:49.022
Okay.

51:49.815 --> 51:52.692
I want you to saw her hands off
at the wrist line.

51:53.194 --> 51:55.862
<i>We gotta have those cuffs for prints.</i>

52:19.220 --> 52:20.220
I can't.

52:20.554 --> 52:23.223
Cut her hands off.
We need the handcuffs.

52:23.766 --> 52:24.974
I can't. No.

52:25.476 --> 52:27.101
Saw off her hands.

52:27.394 --> 52:28.978
<i>Take off the cuffs.</i>

52:29.730 --> 52:30.730
I can't.

52:31.106 --> 52:33.316
Listen to me.
We need those cuffs.

52:33.484 --> 52:34.484
I can't!

52:34.735 --> 52:37.111
-Amelia, we need--
-No! Fuck you!

52:39.615 --> 52:41.908
Amelia! Amelia!

52:47.414 --> 52:51.125
If he wants her hands cut off,
he can come and do it himself!

52:56.841 --> 53:00.760
Amelia? Amelia.

53:05.891 --> 53:07.684
Amelia.

53:25.536 --> 53:27.620
That'll be $1 6.50.

